As part of ongoing effort to curtail the spread of coronavirus, Yobe State Sub-committee on fumigation has begun intense decontamination of no fewer than 100 public premises. .The Chairman, Sub-Committee on  fumigation, who is also the Commissioner for Environment, Sidi Yakubu Karasuwa, disclosed that all public places such as markets, motor parks, public and private offices would be disinfected. He said the exercise would be repeated after every two weeks to ensure environmental safety of these places. He explained that the committee has engaged 27 fire-fighting trucks that would be conducting the exercise in the 17 local government areas with emphasis on major towns of Damaturu, Potiskum, Geidam, Nguru and Gashu’a. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here  COVID-19: Benue fumigates markets, public places LG boss leads fumigation against coronavirus Yobe fumigates graveyards against reptiles